review_blob: The taste is excellent. It is sweat and yeasty, has a compact flavor. Dark fruity character, with prunes and raisins and licorice. Also there are (the usual suspects) caramel ande brown suger - I almost forgot ;). Carbonation is just right for this beer - not to much, but prominent. Hides the alcohol very well, without an excessive sugarly taste. You drink this beer easy, and because of the compact flavor you might think this it is not very complex. But it is in the way the flavors are bound together that makes this beer so good. As if all the complexity comes together in a point of beer singularity (this is the beer talking) controlled by a yet to be discovered force of the universe. So...
Sweet taste of malt, hops and yeast. Very good trapist from Rochefort that tastes like brown sugar.
Dark thick with a taste of coffee chocolate licorice and vanilla. Long lingering bitter taste.
Dark oily with a taste of licorice, chocolate and chili. It has a mild taste of chili nothing agressive but more like an afterburner
